<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDAFFF7FF78F9D2FC5E1F2E" box="[151,920,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDAFFF7FF78F9D2FC5E1F2E" blockId="1.[151,1436,1555,1905]" box="[151,920,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<typeStatus id="A4268864FFDAFFF7FF78F9D2FF091F2E" box="[151,207,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FEDAF9D2FDE31F2E" box="[309,549,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Carinobulus complex</emphasis>
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FDC2F9D2FD401F2E" bold="true" box="[557,646,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDAFFF7FF28F9F6FC991F76" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDAFFF7FF28F9F6FC991F76" blockId="1.[151,1436,1555,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FF28F9F6FED21F52" bold="true" box="[199,276,1591,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Name.</emphasis>
To reflect the bimodally crested metazonae characteristic of the genus, and ʻ-bolusʼ, a common suffix for genus-group names in the 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D4D45FFDAFFF7FE09F99AFDAA1F76" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1895" box="[486,620,1627,1653]" class="Diplopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirobolida" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Spirobolida</taxonomicName>
; masculine in gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDAFFF7FF28F9BFFC7B1E4E" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDAFFF7FF28F9BFFC7B1E4E" blockId="1.[151,1436,1555,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FF28F9BFFE841F9B" bold="true" box="[199,322,1662,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new genus and species is remarkable not only in the bimodally crested metazonae (slightly, but clearly concave in the middle), which in itself is unique in the family, but also in the anterior gonopods being particularly elaborate and complex, multiramous and rather palm-shaped. In addition to the bimodal crests, 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D4D45FFDAFFF7FAFFF906FA5A1FE2" authority="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel" authorityYear="2022" box="[1296,1436,1735,1761]" genus="Carinobolus" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FAFFF906FA5A1FE2" box="[1296,1436,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Carinobolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FF78F92AFEC61E06" bold="true" box="[151,256,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="52DA57AFFFDAFFF7FF78F92AFEC61E06" box="[151,256,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from the similar 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D4D45FFDAFFF7FDE1F92AFD4A1E06" authority="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel, 2022" authorityName="Golovatch &amp; Vandenspiegel" authorityYear="2022" box="[526,652,1771,1797]" class="Diplopoda" family="Pachybolidae" genus="Costabolus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirobolida" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FDE1F92AFD4A1E06" box="[526,652,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Costabolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FD7DF92AFD3D1E06" bold="true" box="[658,763,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="52DA57AFFFDAFFF7FD7DF92AFD3D1E06" box="[658,763,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the absence of prominent prefemoral protuberances from male legs 2 and of prominent coxal protuberances from male legs 3, and by the overall shape of the anterior gonopods which are palm-like rather than subtriangular. See also Key below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3387654DFFDAFFF7FF28F897FB9E1E72" box="[199,1112,1878,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7B2236C6FFDAFFF7FF28F897FB9E1E72" blockId="1.[151,1436,1555,1905]" box="[199,1112,1878,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis id="49E9EAD4FFDAFFF7FF28F897FEA71E73" bold="true" box="[199,353,1878,1904]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="A4268864FFDAFFF7FD8FF896FD561E72" box="[608,656,1879,1905]" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">type</typeStatus>
locality in southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="038A7656FFDAFFF7FC4DF896FC301E72" box="[930,1014,1879,1905]" name="Nigeria" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="E3A62A43FFDAFFF7FBE9F896FB8C1E72" box="[1030,1098,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1191,1215]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1168]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1436,181,1168]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Distributions of Carinobolus complex sp. nov. and Costabolus baculus sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6610066" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6610066/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="98">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
